cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with computational problems related to the convex hull of a stochastic dataset in Euclidean space, which involves geometric insights and algorithms. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the computation of expected statistics, such as diameter, width, and combinatorial complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the paper proposes an exact algorithm for combinatorial complexity, which could also place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
